---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Feliks Mamczur and Prompted Psyche, a research-driven project on AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI Interaction."
>
  <section class="page-shell two-column">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI Interaction.</h1>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Feliks Mamczur writes and consults on AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI
          Interaction.
        </p>
        <p>
          He approaches the subject as a psychology student, author and consultant with a
          creative workflow background in film, editing and post-production.
        </p>
        <p>
          Prompted Psyche is a research-driven publication on the human side of artificial
          intelligence - how AI shapes thought, emotion, trust, communication,
          relationships, creativity and work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h2>Research profile</h2>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Feliks is developing registered research projects on the psychological and
            creative dimensions of Human-AI Interaction, including AI chatbot use, anxiety,
            authorship, authenticity and creative control in AI-assisted practice.
          </p>
          <p>
            These projects are in progress and form part of the research background behind
            Prompted Psyche.
          </p>
          <p>
            ORCID:{' '}
            <a href="https://orcid.org/0009-0001-0715-0517" rel="me noopener">
              https://orcid.org/0009-0001-0715-0517
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          His background in film, editing and post-production informs his understanding of
          narrative, attention, image, emotion and creative workflows. Prompted Psyche is
          not a film portfolio, but this background shapes the way the project approaches
          AI as a cultural, psychological and communicative technology.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
